cs.CG, cs.DS, cs.DM, cs.GR, cs.NA. 

The paper is about a subquadratic algorithm for finding shortest paths on a polyhedron, which is a problem in computational geometry. Therefore, cs.CG (Computational Geometry) is the most likely category. The algorithm involves data structures and graph traversal, so cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) and cs.GR (Graph Theory) are also likely categories. The paper also involves optimization and mathematical programming, which could fall under cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics) and cs.NA (Numerical Analysis).
